	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Let's look at why we have more Warrior only items than you do from an RP standpoint.<BR>
<BR>
Warriors are trained in battle with sword and bladed weapons. We put our whole life<BR>
into training with our weapons to use them efficiently and quickly. Because we put<BR>
more time into training with weapons, we know more about how to use different types<BR>
of weapons. If someone in the age this game seems to be set that was not from Japan <BR>
would pick up a Katana and chop himself to pieces with it because of the different <BR>
balancing and blade. The warrior, however, knows what to look for in balance and <BR>
how sharp the blade is, would be able to wield this weapon somewhat effeciently for <BR>
not having any training with it. (this is relating directly to the Bladestorm because<BR>
it was mentioned earlier on.)<BR>
<BR>
Then, the SK.<BR>
<BR>
The SK begins training in the blade at an early age, but he has something else to get <BR>
in the way as well. He must train in his magical arts. He must master his Harm Touch <BR>
and using Cantrips (small spells that have no effect whatsoever) so he can familiarize <BR>
himself with his art. As a shadowknight picking up a Katana, not as trained in the art <BR>
of the blade as a warrior, would use it as any other 2 handed slashing weapon, using the <BR>
weight of the weapon cleave arms and other appendages from the enemy, and also underestimating <BR>
the true weight of the weapon. The blade on the Katana is sharp, and will almost never break.<BR>
The Shadowknight brings a mighty upward slash, meant to shatter the helmet of the opponent.<BR>
All that happens is the blade falls onto the helmet, making a gouge in it but not enough to <BR>
shatter it. <BR>
<BR>
The warrior, however, realizes that the Katana is used as more of a 1 handed slashing type of weapon,<BR>
using two hands and bringing the Katana across the stomach of the enemy, cleaving his armor like butter <BR>
and slicing skin like bread.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
This is what Katanas are used for, not like most 2 handed swords.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
(In case you are wondering, this information is verified by a person who fancies himself a sword collector and studier, me.)<BR>
<BR>
Well, that is why you don't have as many Shadowknight only weapons, simply because<BR>
there aren't many weapons that a warrior can't pick up and use as well or better <BR>
because of their training. Now, if you come up with something like a Cat o' 9 tails,<BR>
a whip with 9 long barbed strips of leather at the end, that would be more of a <BR>
Shadowknight weapon because Warriors would totally disdain the weapon as dishonorable<BR>
and gross, because Warriors are meant to kill, not cause major pain and leave their enemys alive.<BR>
<BR>
Just my 2 cp... <BR>
I am glad I didn't post this on a Shadowknight board.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
									
